CENAC TOWING COMPANY, Inc., Appellant, v. Ernest J. STOUFFLET, Jr., Appellee. No. 22352. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. March 14, 1966. George B. Matthews, Lemle & Kelleher, New Orleans, La., for appellant. Philip E. Henderson, O’Neal & Waitz, Houma, La., for appellee.

Before RIVES and GEWI.N, Circuit Judges, and ALLGOOD, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

For the reasons well stated in the opinion of the District Court, the judgment is affirmed. 236 F.Supp. 198 (1964).

Affirmed.
